Content:
@MParris, In regard to *"It sounds like you haven't implemented SparkplugB yet, but are interested. If you do implement it, my only request is that you take an honest assessment at how long it takes you to incorporate into your product vs the time it took you to develop the OPC-UA side.":*
I have some experience with SparkPlugB in another project, but yes, our product does not support yet it. As a Developer, I can say that assuming that readily available SDK will be used (not development from scratch, when you start just with the spec in hands), it would take approximately the same effort, no matter what feature you would add - MQTT/SparkPlug or OPC UA PubSub. For example, if you use the OPC UA C++ Client SDK offered by my company, I think designing and writing part of the code in your application related to communication with OPC UA servers would take only days. It will be mostly about GUI, storing configuration data, and doing whatever you want in this application with data received from servers.

I am interested to know, is there a demand for such a feature: publishing data from regular OPC UA Servers to MQTT in SparkPlug format. If so, please contact me, can be done in roughly one month (whole release cycle).
